{"title": "\n\t\t\t  Nobel laureate Luc Montagnier claimed that the coronavirus genome contained sequences of HIV (the virus that causes AIDS).\t\t", "flag": "FALSE:", "url": "https://healthfeedback.org/claimreview/claim-by-nobel-laureate-luc-montagnier-that-the-novel-coronavirus-is-man-made-and-contains-genetic-material-from-hiv-is-inaccurate/", "source": "Genomic analyses of the novel coronavirus show that it was not engineered. In addition, the claim that its genome contains inserted HIV sequences is based on a now-withdrawn preprint of a study that contained significant flaws in design and execution. The so-called \u201cHIV insertions\u201d identified by the authors are in fact gene sequences that can also be found in many other organisms besides HIV.", "country": "United States", "date": "2020/04/17", "keywords":[]}
{"title": "\n\t\t\t  A video argues that the pandemic could have resulted from the accidental or intentional release of either a natural virus under study or an artificial virus that was bioengineered (manmade).\t\t", "flag": "No evidence:", "url": "https://healthfeedback.org/viral-video-promotes-the-unsupported-hypothesis-that-sars-cov-2-is-a-bioengineered-virus-released-from-a-wuhan-research-laboratory/", "source": "In summary, the hypothesis that SARS-CoV-2 is a bioengineered virus released or leaked from a Wuhan research laboratory relies on scientific claims that are either unsupported or false. It ought to be noted, however, that this does not concern the hypothesis of a natural virus being studied and accidentally leaking, for example because of animal escape or infection of laboratory staff.", "country": "United States", "date": "2020/04/16", "keywords":[]}
