{"title": "\n\t\t\t  The coronavirus pandemic can be dramatically slowed, or stopped, with the immediate widespread use of high doses of vitamin C.\t\t", "flag": "No evidence:", "url": "https://healthfeedback.org/claimreview/vitamin-c-supplementation-does-not-prevent-viral-respiratory-infections-such-as-those-caused-by-coronaviruses-in-the-general-population/", "source": "Maintaining an adequate intake of vitamin C is important for staying healthy. However, evidence from clinical trials shows that regular vitamin C supplementation does not prevent viral respiratory tract infections such as the common cold, which can be caused by coronaviruses, in the general population. Although some studies have shown a reduced incidence of the common cold in individuals undergoing severe physical stress, such as marathon runners.", "country": "United States", "date": "2020/02/12", "keywords":[]}
{"title": "\n\t\t\t  The novel coronavirus contains \u201cpShuttle-SN\u201d sequence, proving laboratory origin.\t\t", "flag": "False:", "url": "https://healthfeedback.org/claimreview/2019-novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-does-not-contain-pshuttle-sn-sequence-no-evidence-that-virus-is-man-made/", "source": "The pShuttle-SN vector was designed by researchers seeking to develop a potential SARS vaccine. The new coronavirus does not contain a sequence from the pShuttle-SN vector.", "country": "United States", "date": "2020/02/05", "keywords":[]}
